Description: Handle sliver of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Clay fine light brown; cream slip.
Production date: 172 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes, 2015, 142.)
Curator's comments: Trimmed. Name Nikasagoras. Probably from same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR 092.27.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0905)
